  "prompt": "If I am talking on whatsapp call to someone and another person calls me on my whatsapp. what status will he get. will it show busy?",
  "response": "When you're engaged in a WhatsApp call and someone else attempts to call you on WhatsApp, the following typically occurs:\n\n1. **Caller\u2019s Notification:**\n   - **Status Indication:** The person trying to call you will receive a notification indicating that you're currently on another call. While WhatsApp doesn't explicitly display the word \"busy,\" the status message will effectively communicate that you're unavailable at that moment.\n   - **Call Experience:** The caller might hear a ringtone or see that the call is not immediately connecting, depending on WhatsApp's current interface updates. However, they won't be able to initiate a second call until you're free.\n\n2. **Your Device Behavior:**\n   - **Incoming Call Handling:** On your end, the incoming call attempt will be queued or shown as an incoming call that you can choose to ignore or reject. If you have multiple WhatsApp calls enabled, you might receive a notification for the second incoming call, but typically, WhatsApp allows only one active call at a time.\n   - **User Interface:** Your screen might display both calls, but you'll need to choose which one to continue or switch between them if supported.\n\n3. **Overall Experience:**\n   - **Sequential Calls:** WhatsApp ensures that only one call is active at any given time to maintain call quality and avoid confusion. Subsequent callers are informed of your current call status, preventing overlapping conversations.\n\n**Summary:** While WhatsApp doesn't explicitly label your status as \"busy,\" the app effectively communicates that you're engaged in another call, preventing additional calls from interrupting your ongoing conversation.",
